                </a>
            </div>

            <h2 id="ds_credentials" class="size-20">What is the DCRA Collection Program?</h2>
            <p>The DCRA Collection Program collects all mandatory reports as defined by the DCRA of 2013 (P.L. 113-242). The Act requires reporting for each fiscal year, beginning with Fiscal Year 2016.</p>
            <p>The U.S. Department of Justice has designated the Bureau of Justice Statistics (BJS) to collect all federal law enforcement agency reports as required by the DCRA of 2013 (P.L. 113-242). To collect these reports, BJS will conduct a survey of federal agencies with law enforcement, detention, and/or incarceration functions.</p>
            <p>Active data collection under the FDCRP has been temporarily postponed while BJS reviews the design of the survey. BJS will begin collecting information about deaths that occurred in FY 2018 shortly. Federal law enforcement agencies that fall under the reporting requirements specified in the Act will be contacted at that time to participate in the survey.</p>
            <p>If you have any questions, please contact <a href="mailto:jessica.stroop@usdoj.gov">Jessica Stroop</a>, Federal Death in Custody Reporting Program Manager, BJS.</p>
            <div class="divider divider-border divider-right">
