                </a>
            </div>

            <h2 id="ds_errors" class="size-20">What is the Bureau of Justice Statistics?</h2>
            <p>The U.S. Department of Justice has designated the Bureau of Justice Statistics (BJS) to collect all federal law enforcement agency reports as required by the DCRA of 2013 (P.L. 113-242). BJS is the principal statistical agency of the U.S. Department of Justice. BJS' primary function is the compilation and analysis of criminal justice data and the dissemination of information for statistical purposes.</p>
