            <h2 id="ds_saveprint" class="size-20">What is the Purpose of the DCRA Data Collection Forms?</h2>
            <p><b><i>CJ-13: DCRA Annual Summary Form</i></b>- Requests federal law enforcement agencies to identify all deaths under DCRA, occurring in a given fiscal year.</p>
            <p><b><i>CJ-13A: Arrest-Related Death Incident Report</i></b>- For each identified arrest related-death, federal law enforcement agencies provide information on decedent characteristics and circumstances surrounding the death.</p>
            <p><b><i>CJ-13B: Detention/Incarceration Death Incident Report</i></b>- For each identified detention/ incarceration death, federal law enforcement agencies provide information on decedent characteristics and circumstances surrounding the death.</p>
